<subSubSection id="61BEAAA5C35C3750249CFA5D1F38FD59" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="2875" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="291BF92EC35C375F249CFA5D1BF6FA37" blockId="7.[143,1103,1436,1691]" box="[143,251,1436,1459]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874">
<heading id="72534E42C35C375F249CFA5D1BF6FA37" box="[143,251,1436,1459]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874" reason="5">
<emphasis id="1BD0253CC35C375F249CFA5D1BF6FA37" box="[143,251,1436,1459]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="291BF92EC35C3750249CFA021A66FE5A" blockId="7.[143,1103,1436,1691]" lastBlockId="8.[211,1172,167,733]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="2875" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874">
<taxonomicName id="EEA482ADC35C375F249CFA021BE3FA5F" box="[143,238,1475,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Liotesba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BD0253CC35C375F249CFA021BE3FA5F" box="[143,238,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874">Liotesba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other genera within the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="EEA482ADC35C375F27ADFA031F42FA5E" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[958,1103,1474,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xantholinini">Xantholinini</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: (a) body subcylindrical, usually medium to large in size (
<quantity id="EE5C54CBC35C375F2484F9C31A0BF99E" box="[151,262,1538,1562]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="7.0">7–12 mm</quantity>
), more rarely larger (
<quantity id="EE5C54CBC35C375F25E5F9C3197FF99E" box="[502,626,1538,1562]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="2874" unit="mm" value="14.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="12.0">12–17 mm</quantity>
); (b) head subquadrate or subrectangular, with sparse-scattered large punctures, almost without microsculpture; (c) frontal furrow often short or not obvious, ocular furrows usually missing; (d) antennomere II shorter than III; (e) labrum with four teeth; (f) second segment of maxillary palpi and last segment of labial palpi usually longest; (g) gular sutures not fused together, separated by the deeply excavated gular plate; (h) neck wide, about half of head width; (i) pronotum with two large anterolateral punctures, and one posterolateral puncture (
<figureCitation id="B19FE5ABC353375024CFFF261A5FFF7B" box="[220,338,231,255]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="9.[143,210,1472,1494]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,162,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-6@9.[144,1104,162,1439]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 1. Liotesba fengyangshana sp. nov., (A) forebody (a. anterolateral puncture = antennal puncture; b. midlateral puncture = ocular puncture; c. temporal puncture; d. occipital puncture; e: anterolateral puncture; f. posterolateral puncture; g. anteocular furrow = ocular furrow; h. anterior portion of basal bulb); (B) labrum; (C) right mandible; (D) maxillary palpus; (E) labial palpus; (F) male tergite VIII; (G) male sternite VIII; (H) male tergite X = male tergite of genital segment; (I) male sternite IX = male sternite of genital segment; (J) aedeagus, dorsal view; (K) aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars 0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5198104" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5198104/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">Figure 1A</figureCitation>
:e, f) on each side; (j) antesternal plate with a longitudinal medium furrow; (k) superior line of hypomeron bending toward prosternum before anterior angle of pronotum, but not joining inferior line; (l) mesoventrite with distinctly projecting, longitudinal median ridge; (m) protarsi dilated; tibiae with apical ctenidium, without subapical ctenidia; (n) aedeagus subelliptical or subovoid at base, with a pair of black sclerites near apex of median lobe; (o) female genital segments comprising a distinct oblong sternite, and a pair of subtriangular sclerites in ventral side (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="4D3584DFC353375027FFFE671F82FE3A" author="Bordoni A" box="[1004,1167,422,446]" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875" pagination="1 - 998" refId="ref17034" refString="Bordoni A. 2002. Xantholinini of the Oriental Region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Classification, phylogeny and taxonomic revision. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali Monografie (Turin). 33: 1 - 998." type="journal article" year="2002">Bordoni, 2002</bibRefCitation>
, p. 67: fig. 69).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="291BF92EC353375024EDFE271F38FD59" blockId="8.[211,1172,167,733]" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">
According to our knowledge of the distributional ranges of all 
<taxonomicName id="EEA482ADC353375027CEFE261F9EFE7A" box="[989,1171,486,511]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Liotesba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="1BD0253CC353375027CEFE261F31FE7B" box="[989,1084,487,511]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">Liotesba</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="B19FE5ABC353375024CFFDC71A34FD9A" box="[220,313,518,542]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="20.[211,278,961,983]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,167,928]" captionTargetId="figure-5@20.[212,1172,167,928]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 5. Geographical distribution of species of the genus Liotesba Scheerpeltz. L. fengyangshana sp. nov. (); L. expansipalpis sp. nov. (); L. recticeps sp. nov. (); L. ovaticeps sp. nov. (); L. enthymema Bordoni (); L. hubeiana Bordoni (); L. itoi Bordoni (); L. oculifera Bordoni (); L. punctiventris (Sharp) (); L. malaisei Scheerpeltz (); L. rubescens Bordoni (); L. rubra Bordoni (); L. rufula Bordoni (); L. subsimilis (Cameron) (); L. siamensis Bordoni (); L. wittmeri Coiffait (); L. antonellae Bordoni ()." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5198116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5198116/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">Figure 5</figureCitation>
), the genus 
<taxonomicName id="EEA482ADC353375025ADFDC71910FD9A" box="[446,541,518,542]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Liotesba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BD0253CC353375025ADFDC71910FD9A" box="[446,541,518,542]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">Liotesba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be an element of the Oriental region. The species are distributed along the south boundary of the Tibet Plateau toward the monsoon region of eastern Asia (from 
<collectingCountry id="51B3B9BEC35337502608FD87198FFDDA" box="[539,642,582,606]" name="Thailand" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">Thailand</collectingCountry>
across mainland 
<collectingCountry id="51B3B9BEC3533750275AFD871883FDDA" box="[841,910,582,606]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">China</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="51B3B9BEC353375027A6FD871F05FDDA" box="[949,1032,582,606]" name="Taiwan" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="51B3B9BEC35337502051FD871F85FDDA" box="[1090,1160,582,606]" name="Japan" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">Japan</collectingCountry>
). Only 
<taxonomicName id="EEA482ADC35337502500FDA61A93FDFA" authorityName="Tempora" baseAuthorityName="Cameron" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[275,414,614,638]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Liotesba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsimilis">
<emphasis id="1BD0253CC35337502500FDA61A93FDFA" box="[275,414,614,638]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">L. subsimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EEA482ADC353375025BDFDA61956FDFA" authorityName="Distance" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[430,603,615,638]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Liotesba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctiventris">
<emphasis id="1BD0253CC353375025BDFDA61956FDFA" box="[430,603,615,638]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">L. punctiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
