<taxonomicName id="EEA482ADC35337502685FDA6181FFDFA" authorityName="Scheerpeltz" authorityYear="1965" box="[662,786,614,638]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Liotesba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis id="1BD0253CC35337502685FDA6181FFDFA" box="[662,786,614,638]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="2875">L. malaisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are widespread. There are apparently two diversity hotspots. First, the southwest boundary of the Himalaya, where seven endemic species and two widespread species were found. Second, the Chinese mainland from where six endemic and two widespread species were recorded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
